    "attributes": {
        "action": "Increase funding for care for people with Spinal Cord Injury",
        "additional_details": "This petition is asking for more funding for the NHS & their staff, to receive the necessary training to support those with SCI & cater for their basic needs, when admitted to a general hospital. \r\n\r\nThe current lack of knowledge , understanding & training is putting people with SCI at risk of further illness or disability. \r\n\r\nThis is not just a health issue but a human rights issue & more funding is required to ensure NHS have the training they need, to support SCI patients.",
        "background": "More funding for NHS staff training to support & cater for the basic needs  of  Spinal Cord Injury patients when being re-admitted to a general hospital",
